{"type":"message","id":"7491c2e7","parentId":"23d8a818","timestamp":"2026-03-20T08:57:33.331Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"openpyxl and xlrd are available, but xlwt is not. I'll use openpyxl to create the output .xlsx files. Let me write the complete script.\n\nThe plan:\n1. Read the source data (CSV/Excel exported from Impala) \n2. Read the template structure using xlrd to understand field positions\n3. Use openpyxl to create each taxpayer's file from the template, preserving formatting as much as possible\n\nSince the original .xls has complex merged cells and formatting, I'll use a hybrid approach:\n- Use xlrd to read the source data content\n- Use openpyxl to write the output with basic styling\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. \n\nThe template's merged cell structure makes direct copying complex, so the most practical approach is to parse the template with xlrd to understand the layout, then use openpyxl to programmatically populate each taxpayer's file while maintaining the merged cell structure and applying reasonable styling. I'll write a comprehensive Python script that reads the source data and template, then generates individual files organized by district. I'm looking at the remaining template fields to understand the complete data structure I'll need to work with—things like tax declarations, current balances, enforcement measures, and financial information about the taxpayer and their related entities. 现在我需要设计完整的脚本架构。我会使用xlrd读取源数据，然后用openpyxl创建每个纳税人的Excel文件，并保留合并单元格和格式。关键是理解模板中每个字段的位置，这样才能正确填充数据。我先写一个能够解析模板结构、读取源数据并生成单个纳税人文件的脚本。\n\n对于格式化输出，我会尽量保留原始模板的字体、颜色和合并单元格设置。 输出文件格式\n2. Field mapping\n\nLet me write the full script.\n\nFor field mapping, the user said their Impala data has one row per taxpayer. I need to know the column names in their Impala data. I'll make the script flexible by accepting column name mapping.\n\nLet me design the template structure first:\n\nThe template uses a 8-column layout with merged cells. The structure is:\n- Column [0]: 序号 (number/index) \n- Column [1]: 项目 (field name)\n- Column [2-4]: various data columns depending on section\n- Column [3]: 填列内容 (content to fill) \n- Column [5]: 备注 (remarks)\n- Column [6-7]: sometimes extra info\n\nThe sections in the template all follow the same pattern, so I can reuse the same rendering function for each section. Now I'll write the complete script that reads the template, populates it with taxpayer data, and saves the output as .xlsx files organized by district.","thinkingSignature":"365c7e5c77f6a56526113d76545ff18e72c0a6c125c3852e64e91fb703fdad7c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5egzrc7pf2sv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport xlrd\nf = '/Users/ling/.openclaw/media/inbound/欠税企业调查情况表3.17---92b6e6e2-0f6e-46b4-806d-99bc6627515d'\nwb = xlrd.open_workbook(f, formatting_info=True)\nws = wb.sheet_by_index(0)\n\n# Check merged cells\nprint('Merged cells:', wb.sheet_by_index(0).merged_cells)\n\n# Check XF info for some cells\nprint()\nprint('Column widths:')\nfor c in range(ws.ncols):\n    width = ws.col_width(c)\n    if width > 0:\n        print(f'  Col {c}: width={width}')\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22065,"output":733,"cacheRead":24939,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47737,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773997025911}}
