{"type":"message","id":"ecc4b2ae","parentId":"99602b9f","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:10:58.780Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<active-task-guard>\nSource: /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md\nStatus: active\nUse this only as the recovery rail for the current multi-step task.\nIf the user's latest message is a continuation, continue from Current, update ACTIVE_TASK.md after each minimum deliverable, and immediately promote the next item.\nIf the user's latest message is clearly unrelated, do not force this task.\n\nGoal:\n- 梳理当前量化系统的 P0/P1 级漏洞与数据源风险，评估引入国泰海通 PTrade 数据的实用性，并给出是否值得投入的判断与优先级建议\n\nAcceptance:\n- 明确当前主要数据源（特别是行情、成交、账户）存在的关键风险点和 P0/P1 漏洞清单\n- 对国泰海通 PTrade 客户端的数据质量做出基于公开信息和行业经验的判断，给出“值得/不值得”引入的结论\n- 如结论为“值得”，提出一版按性价比排序的接入优先级与简要实施策略；如结论为“不值得”，说明理由并列出替代方向\n\nCurrent:\n- 梳理现有系统的数据链路与痛点，形成 P0/P1 漏洞清单\n\nNext:\n- 根据结论，给出 PTrade 接入或替代方案的优先级建议\n\nRecent Evidence:\n- /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/research/reports/ptrade_windows_bridge_plan_20260320.md\n- /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/research/reports/ptrade_data_quality_assessment_20260320.md\n- 2026-03-20 16:49：补充判断——同花顺/投资账本在 Mac 上可读取持仓与交易，但更适合作为账户信息补丁层，不等同于券商交易事实层；PTrade 的主要价值仍在真实委托状态与账户事实闭环。\n\nIntegrity Warnings:\n- None\n\nBlockers:\n- None\n</active-task-guard>\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54e4f71b6448c4f64a2e6b08efe\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-20 16:55 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54e4f71b6448c4f64a2e6b08efe]\nou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7: 我现在需要写代码从impala平台提取这些数据，但是提取的数据是一个纳税人只有一行数据，我现在需要你写一段python代码，能够将一张表里有上百个纳税人数据（每一个纳税人的数据为一行），生成每一个纳税人一张这个欠税企业调查情况表，除此之外，我有7个区县局，分别是自流井、贡井、大安、沿滩、荣县、富顺、高新，每一个区县形成一个文件夹，里面放着你生成的分户的欠税企业调查情况表"}],"timestamp":1773997858779}}
{"type":"message","id":"bcd85794","parentId":"ecc4b2ae","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:11:15.422Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Evaluating task execution**\n\nI need to clarify what the instructions say about before replying. It states that I should scan for skills, and if one clearly fits, I should read its SKILL.md. So I’ll start with the coding-agent SKILL.md. Memory search and inspecting the active task may not be necessary since they seem unrelated. Although AGENTS suggests I read the ACTIVE_TASK if it exists, it seems like that’s already injected. I'll likely need to create a script file in the workspace, possibly using an uploaded XLS template as input.**Simplifying code creation**\n\nTo make things easier, I could use openpyxl to create a new workbook from scratch with merged cells and fixed labels, rather than trying to keep the exact style. The user’s request, \"一张这个欠税企业调查情况表,\" suggests they want a similar layout. I can generate an xlsx file with the same structure and fill in the values instead of preserving the original xls style. While the user asked for code, we don't need to run it immediately, so I can write a script with mapping and folder structure. I'll need to inspect the template to build the layout efficiently.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_co7MfQIQ3w2tsBfqzo4UoygA","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/coding-agent/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773997858780}}
{"type":"message","id":"b395bd98","parentId":"bcd85794","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:11:15.505Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_co7MfQIQ3w2tsBfqzo4UoygA","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: coding-agent\ndescription: 'Delegate coding tasks to Codex, Claude Code, or Pi agents via background process. Use when: (1) building/creating new features or apps, (2) reviewing PRs (spawn in temp dir), (3) refactoring large codebases, (4) iterative coding that needs file exploration. NOT for: simple one-liner fixes (just edit), reading code (use read tool), thread-bound ACP harness requests in chat (for example spawn/run Codex or Claude Code in a Discord thread; use sessions_spawn with runtime:\"acp\"), or any work in ~/clawd workspace (never spawn agents here). Claude Code: use --print --permission-mode bypassPermissions (no PTY). Codex/Pi/OpenCode: pty:true required.'\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\": { \"emoji\": \"🧩\", \"requires\": { \"anyBins\": [\"claude\", \"codex\", \"opencode\", \"pi\"] } },\n  }\n---\n\n# Coding Agent (bash-first)\n\nUse **bash** (with optional background mode) for all coding agent work. Simple and effective.\n\n## ⚠️ PTY Mode: Codex/Pi/OpenCode yes, Claude Code no\n\nFor **Codex, Pi, and OpenCode**, PTY is still required (interactive terminal apps):\n\n```bash\n# ✅ Correct for Codex/Pi/OpenCode\nbash pty:true command:\"codex exec 'Your prompt'\"\n```\n\nFor **Claude Code** (`claude` CLI), use `--print --permission-mode bypassPermissions` instead.\n`--dangerously-skip-permissions` with PTY can exit after the confirmation dialog.\n`--print` mode keeps full tool access and avoids interactive confirmation:\n\n```bash\n# ✅ Correct for Claude Code (no PTY needed)\ncd /path/to/project && claude --permission-mode bypassPermissions --print 'Your task'\n\n# For background execution: use background:true on the exec tool\n\n# ❌ Wrong for Claude Code\nbash pty:true command:\"claude --dangerously-skip-permissions 'task'\"\n```\n\n### Bash Tool Parameters\n\n| Parameter    | Type    | Description                                                                 |\n| ------------ | ------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| `command`    | string  | The shell command to run                                                    |\n| `pty`        | boolean | **Use for coding agents!** Allocates a pseudo-terminal for interactive CLIs |\n| `workdir`    | string  | Working directory (agent sees only this folder's context)                   |\n| `background` | boolean | Run in background, returns sessionId for monitoring                         |\n| `timeout`    | number  | Timeout in seconds (kills process on expiry)                                |\n| `elevated`   | boolean | Run on host instead of sandbox (if allowed)                                 |\n\n### Process Tool Actions (for background sessions)\n\n| Action      | Description                                          |\n| ----------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |\n| `list`      | List all running/recent sessions                     |\n| `poll`      | Check if session is still running                    |\n| `log`       | Get session output (with optional offset/limit)      |\n| `write`     | Send raw data to stdin                               |\n| `submit`    | Send data + newline (like typing and pressing Enter) |\n| `send-keys` | Send key tokens or hex bytes                         |\n| `paste`     | Paste text (with optional bracketed mode)            |\n| `kill`      | Terminate the session                                |\n\n---\n\n## Quick Start: One-Shot Tasks\n\nFor quick prompts/chats, create a temp git repo and run:\n\n```bash\n# Quick chat (Codex needs a git repo!)\nSCRATCH=$(mktemp -d) && cd $SCRATCH && git init && codex exec \"Your prompt here\"\n\n# Or in a real project - with PTY!\nbash pty:true workdir:~/Projects/myproject command:\"codex exec 'Add error handling to the API calls'\"\n```\n\n**Why git init?** Codex refuses to run outside a trusted git directory. Creating a temp repo solves this for scratch work.\n\n---\n\n## The Pattern: workdir + background + pty\n\nFor longer tasks, use background mode with PTY:\n\n```bash\n# Start agent in target directory (with PTY!)\nbash pty:true workdir:~/project background:true command:\"codex exec --full-auto 'Build a snake game'\"\n# Returns sessionId for tracking\n\n# Monitor progress\nprocess action:log sessionId:XXX\n\n# Check if done\nprocess action:poll sessionId:XXX\n\n# Send input (if agent asks a question)\nprocess action:write sessionId:XXX data:\"y\"\n\n# Submit with Enter (like typing \"yes\" and pressing Enter)\nprocess action:submit sessionId:XXX data:\"yes\"\n\n# Kill if needed\nprocess action:kill sessionId:XXX\n```\n\n**Why workdir matters:** Agent wakes up in a focused directory, doesn't wander off reading unrelated files (like your soul.md 😅).\n\n---\n\n## Codex CLI\n\n**Model:** `gpt-5.2-codex` is the default (set in ~/.codex/config.toml)\n\n### Flags\n\n| Flag            | Effect                                             |\n| --------------- | -------------------------------------------------- |\n| `exec \"prompt\"` | One-shot execution, exits when done                |\n| `--full-auto`   | Sandboxed but auto-approves in workspace           |\n| `--yolo`        | NO sandbox, NO approvals (fastest, most dangerous) |\n\n### Building/Creating\n\n```bash\n# Quick one-shot (auto-approves) - remember PTY!\nbash pty:true workdir:~/project command:\"codex exec --full-auto 'Build a dark mode toggle'\"\n\n# Background for longer work\nbash pty:true workdir:~/project background:true command:\"codex --yolo 'Refactor the auth module'\"\n```\n\n### Reviewing PRs\n\n**⚠️ CRITICAL: Never review PRs in OpenClaw's own project folder!**\nClone to temp folder or use git worktree.\n\n```bash\n# Clone to temp for safe review\nREVIEW_DIR=$(mktemp -d)\ngit clone https://github.com/user/repo.git $REVIEW_DIR\ncd $REVIEW_DIR && gh pr checkout 130\nbash pty:true workdir:$REVIEW_DIR command:\"codex review --base origin/main\"\n# Clean up after: trash $REVIEW_DIR\n\n# Or use git worktree (keeps main intact)\ngit worktree add /tmp/pr-130-review pr-130-branch\nbash pty:true workdir:/tmp/pr-130-review command:\"codex review --base main\"\n```\n\n### Batch PR Reviews (parallel army!)\n\n```bash\n# Fetch all PR refs first\ngit fetch origin '+refs/pull/*/head:refs/remotes/origin/pr/*'\n\n# Deploy the army - one Codex per PR (all with PTY!)\nbash pty:true workdir:~/project background:true command:\"codex exec 'Review PR #86. git diff origin/main...origin/pr/86'\"\nbash pty:true workdir:~/project background:true command:\"codex exec 'Review PR #87. git diff origin/main...origin/pr/87'\"\n\n# Monitor all\nprocess action:list\n\n# Post results to GitHub\ngh pr comment <PR#> --body \"<review content>\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Claude Code\n\n```bash\n# Foreground\nbash workdir:~/project command:\"claude --permission-mode bypassPermissions --print 'Your task'\"\n\n# Background\nbash workdir:~/project background:true command:\"claude --permission-mode bypassPermissions --print 'Your task'\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## OpenCode\n\n```bash\nbash pty:true workdir:~/project command:\"opencode run 'Your task'\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Pi Coding Agent\n\n```bash\n# Install: npm install -g @mariozechner/pi-coding-agent\nbash pty:true workdir:~/project command:\"pi 'Your task'\"\n\n# Non-interactive mode (PTY still recommended)\nbash pty:true command:\"pi -p 'Summarize src/'\"\n\n# Different provider/model\nbash pty:true command:\"pi --provider openai --model gpt-4o-mini -p 'Your task'\"\n```\n\n**Note:** Pi now has Anthropic prompt caching enabled (PR #584, merged Jan 2026)!\n\n---\n\n## Parallel Issue Fixing with git worktrees\n\nFor fixing multiple issues in parallel, use git worktrees:\n\n```bash\n# 1. Create worktrees for each issue\ngit worktree add -b fix/issue-78 /tmp/issue-78 main\ngit worktree add -b fix/issue-99 /tmp/issue-99 main\n\n# 2. Launch Codex in each (background + PTY!)\nbash pty:true workdir:/tmp/issue-78 background:true command:\"pnpm install && codex --yolo 'Fix issue #78: <description>. Commit and push.'\"\nbash pty:true workdir:/tmp/issue-99 background:true command:\"pnpm install && codex --yolo 'Fix issue #99 from the approved ticket summary. Implement only the in-scope edits and commit after review.'\"\n\n# 3. Monitor progress\nprocess action:list\nprocess action:log sessionId:XXX\n\n# 4. Create PRs after fixes\ncd /tmp/issue-78 && git push -u origin fix/issue-78\ngh pr create --repo user/repo --head fix/issue-78 --title \"fix: ...\" --body \"...\"\n\n# 5. Cleanup\ngit worktree remove /tmp/issue-78\ngit worktree remove /tmp/issue-99\n```\n\n---\n\n## ⚠️ Rules\n\n1. **Use the right execution mode per agent**:\n   - Codex/Pi/OpenCode: `pty:true`\n   - Claude Code: `--print --permission-mode bypassPermissions` (no PTY required)\n2. **Respect tool choice** - if user asks for Codex, use Codex.\n   - Orchestrator mode: do NOT hand-code patches yourself.\n   - If an agent fails/hangs, respawn it or ask the user for direction, but don't silently take over.\n3. **Be patient** - don't kill sessions because they're \"slow\"\n4. **Monitor with process:log** - check progress without interfering\n5. **--full-auto for building** - auto-approves changes\n6. **vanilla for reviewing** - no special flags needed\n7. **Parallel is OK** - run many Codex processes at once for batch work\n8. **NEVER start Codex in ~/.openclaw/** - it'll read your soul docs and get weird ideas about the org chart!\n9. **NEVER checkout branches in ~/Projects/openclaw/** - that's the LIVE OpenClaw instance!\n\n---\n\n## Progress Updates (Critical)\n\nWhen you spawn coding agents in the background, keep the user in the loop.\n\n- Send 1 short message when you start (what's running + where).\n- Then only update again when something changes:\n  - a milestone completes (build finished, tests passed)\n  - the agent asks a question / needs input\n  - you hit an error or need user action\n  - the agent finishes (include what changed + where)\n- If you kill a session, immediately say you killed it and why.\n\nThis prevents the user from seeing only \"Agent failed before reply\" and having no idea what happened.\n\n---\n\n## Auto-Notify on Completion\n\nFor long-running background tasks, append a wake trigger to your prompt so OpenClaw gets notified immediately when the agent finishes (instead of waiting for the next heartbeat):\n\n```\n... your task here.\n\nWhen completely finished, run this command to notify me:\nopenclaw system event --text \"Done: [brief summary of what was built]\" --mode now\n```\n\n**Example:**\n\n```bash\nbash pty:true workdir:~/project background:true command:\"codex --yolo exec 'Build a REST API for todos.\n\nWhen completely finished, run: openclaw system event --text \\\"Done: Built todos REST API with CRUD endpoints\\\" --mode now'\"\n```\n\nThis triggers an immediate wake event — Skippy gets pinged in seconds, not 10 minutes.\n\n---\n\n## Learnings (Jan 2026)\n\n- **PTY is essential:** Coding agents are interactive terminal apps. Without `pty:true`, output breaks or agent hangs.\n- **Git repo required:** Codex won't run outside a git directory. Use `mktemp -d && git init` for scratch work.\n- **exec is your friend:** `codex exec \"prompt\"` runs and exits cleanly - perfect for one-shots.\n- **submit vs write:** Use `submit` to send input + Enter, `write` for raw data without newline.\n- **Sass works:** Codex responds well to playful prompts. Asked it to write a haiku about being second fiddle to a space lobster, got: _\"Second chair, I code / Space lobster sets the tempo / Keys glow, I follow\"_ 🦞\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773997875495}}
{"type":"message","id":"14ae5f53","parentId":"b395bd98","timestamp":"2026-03-20T09:12:32.852Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Drafting Python Code Snippet**\n\nI need to create a Python code snippet that reads a data file containing taxpayer information, likely generated via Impala, probably in CSV or Excel format. Since I can't assume the environment has Pandas installed, I’ll keep dependencies minimal and consider using Python's built-in 'csv' module for parsing. I should design the function to handle both CSV and Excel, but I'll assume they prefer CSV for export based on Impala’s typical output.**Designing Code with Flexibility**\n\nTo be cautious, I’ll start the code using `pandas.read_csv` or `read_table`, as the user might prefer that. However, I can't assume Pandas is installed in their environment. Since they haven't asked me to run the code here, my focus is on just providing them with working code. It’s common to use Pandas in these tasks. I also need to map columns based on the earlier template I inspected, including their row and column positions.**Computing Data Mapping**\n\nI’m mapping out the data fields based on the earlier execution output. This includes specific columns and their content, like `Row0` with the title '欠税企业调查情况表' and `Row1` noting the currency unit. It seems like I’ll have to list various taxpayer fields, including identification numbers and names, tax jurisdictions, and statuses. However, I notice the requirement states that each taxpayer only has one row of data, indicating they'll have aggregated information rather than multiple entries or events.**Designing for Data Limitations**\n\nSince each taxpayer only has one row of data, it means that subsections allowing for multiple entries won't have detailed information — they might be aggregated or even blank. I can't reconstruct multi-row details, so the script will primarily focus on filling out the top-level items and any existing aggregated fields. I'll also consider designing a mapping dictionary to help the users align their column names with template cell addresses, given that they didn’t specify the columns.**Mapping Template and Script Design**\n\nI’m setting up a mapping for the columns in the template, like defining `COLUMN_MAP` for fields such as `taxpayer_id` and `taxpayer_name`. The template has specific requirements, including using `openpyxl` to load an `.xlsx` file, though currently, we have an `.xls` format. They should ideally convert it to `.xlsx` manually using WPS or Excel. My script will read data from a CSV, create folders for districts, and fill in the template for each taxpayer, ensuring file names are valid. I’ll provide a high-level explanation along with the full script.**Refining File Generation Logic**\n\nI'm mapping row elements like '纳税人名称' to corresponding cells in the Excel template. For sections like '税款追征入库', I clearly define where each data point should go, though I'm recognizing that we might not need excessive detail here since the user specified one row per taxpayer. To keep things flexible, I plan to create a `FIELD_MAPPING` that corresponds each field in the template to incoming data.  \n\nFor the district names, I want to ensure that if a district is unknown, we categorize it as '其他'. I also need to devise a file-naming strategy for saving taxpayer data while ensuring sanitized filenames. I'm configuring the script to handle both CSV and Excel input formats dynamically. This keeps it simple and efficient for the user to create their reports.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"下面直接给你一份可以用的脚本思路 + 代码，你只需要改 3 个路径/列名就能跑。\n\n**前置假设（可以按你实际情况改）：**\n\n- 从 Impala 导出的结果在一个文件里（建议 CSV 或 xlsx），**一行=一个纳税人**。\n- 这张表里列名尽量和模板里的字段一致，比如：`纳税人识别号`、`纳税人名称`、`市（州）局`、`区县局`、`主管税务机关`、`税管员`、`纳税人状态`、`实际行业` 等。\n- 你把刚才那份 `欠税企业调查情况表3.17.xls` 用 WPS/Excel **另存为 xlsx**，比如叫：`欠税企业调查情况表模板.xlsx`（方便用 openpyxl 直接保留格式）。\n\n---\n\n**Python 脚本示例**\n\n```python\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\n\n\"\"\"\n功能：\n- 读取 Impala 导出的汇总表（每行一个纳税人）\n- 按模板《欠税企业调查情况表》为每个纳税人生成一份 Excel\n- 按区县局（自流井、贡井、大安、沿滩、荣县、富顺、高新）分文件夹存放\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport re\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom openpyxl import load_workbook\n\n\n# ======= 1. 路径参数（按你实际情况修改） =======\n\n# 模板路径：请先把欠税企业调查情况表3.17.xls 另存为 .xlsx\nTEMPLATE_PATH = \"欠税企业调查情况表模板.xlsx\"\n\n# Impala 导出的源数据文件：支持 .csv / .xls / .xlsx\nINPUT_DATA_PATH = \"impala_欠税企业汇总表.csv\"\n\n# 输出根目录\nOUTPUT_ROOT = \"输出_欠税企业调查情况表\"\n\n\n# 7 个区县局名称（和数据里“区县局”列的取值一致最好）\nDISTRICTS = [\"自流井\", \"贡井\", \"大安\", \"沿滩\", \"荣县\", \"富顺\", \"高新\"]\n\n# 源数据中表示区县局的列名\nDISTRICT_COLUMN = \"区县局\"\n\n\n# ======= 2. 模板字段映射：源表列名 -> 模板单元格 =======\n# 这些行对应模板中“企业基本情况”部分，都是填到“填列内容”那一列（D 列）\nFIELD_CELL_MAP = {\n    \"纳税人识别号\": \"D5\",\n    \"纳税人名称\": \"D6\",\n    \"市（州）局\": \"D7\",\n    \"区县局\": \"D8\",\n    \"主管税务机关\": \"D9\",\n    \"税管员\": \"D10\",\n    \"纳税人状态\": \"D11\",\n    \"实际行业\": \"D12\",\n    \"发票授信额度\": \"D13\",\n    \"纳税信用等级\": \"D14\",\n    \"增值税申报金额\": \"D15\",      # 2026 年以来申报金额\n    \"发票开具金额\": \"D16\",        # 2026 年以来开票金额\n    \"当前货币资金余额\": \"D17\",\n    \"当前欠税余额\": \"D18\",\n    \"在营情况\": \"D19\",\n    # 如果你的汇总表里还有其他汇总字段，可以继续往下加：\n    # 例如：\"税款追征入库合计金额\": \"D23\",\n}\n\n\n# ======= 3. 工具函数 =======\n\ndef safe_filename(s: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"去掉文件名中的非法字符\"\"\"\n    s = str(s).strip()\n    if not s:\n        return \"未命名\"\n    # 去掉 Windows 不允许的字符\n    s = re.sub(r'[\\\\/:*?\"<>|]', \"_\", s)\n    return s\n\n\ndef load_table(path: str) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    \"\"\"根据扩展名自动读取 CSV 或 Excel\"\"\"\n    ext = os.path.splitext(path)[1].lower()\n    if ext in [\".xls\", \".xlsx\"]:\n        return pd.read_excel(path)\n    elif ext in [\".csv\", \".txt\"]:\n        # 如果是制表符分隔可以加上 sep=\"\\t\"\n        return pd.read_csv(path)\n    else:\n        raise ValueError(f\"不支持的源数据文件类型: {ext}\")\n\n\n# ======= 4. 主逻辑 =======\n\ndef generate_forms():\n    # 1）准备输出目录\n    os.makedirs(OUTPUT_ROOT, exist_ok=True)\n    for d in DISTRICTS:\n        os.makedirs(os.path.join(OUTPUT_ROOT, d), exist_ok=True)\n    # 额外的“其他”目录，用于区县局列里出现意外值\n    other_dir = os.path.join(OUTPUT_ROOT, \"其他\")\n    os.makedirs(other_dir, exist_ok=True)\n\n    # 2）读取源数据\n    df = load_table(INPUT_DATA_PATH)\n    has_district_col = DISTRICT_COLUMN in df.columns\n\n    # 3）逐行生成纳税人表\n    for idx, row in df.iterrows():\n        # ---- 3.1 区县局 / 目标文件夹 ----\n        if has_district_col:\n            district = str(row[DISTRICT_COLUMN]).strip()\n        else:\n            district = \"其他\"\n\n        if district in DISTRICTS:\n            out_dir = os.path.join(OUTPUT_ROOT, district)\n        else:\n            out_dir = other_dir\n        os.makedirs(out_dir, exist_ok=True)\n\n        # ---- 3.2 打开模板并选择工作表 ----\n        wb = load_workbook(TEMPLATE_PATH)\n        if \"调查表\" in wb.sheetnames:\n            ws = wb[\"调查表\"]\n        else:\n            ws = wb.active  # 如果改过名字，就用第一个 Sheet\n\n        # ---- 3.3 填充字段 ----\n        for col_name, cell_addr in FIELD_CELL_MAP.items():\n            if col_name in df.columns:\n                value = row[col_name]\n                # 跳过 NaN\n                if pd.isna(value):\n                    continue\n                ws[cell_addr] = value\n\n        # ---- 3.4 生成文件名 ----\n        taxpayer_name = (\n            row[\"纳税人名称\"] if \"纳税人名称\" in df.columns else f\"纳税人{idx + 1}\"\n        )\n        taxpayer_id = row[\"纳税人识别号\"] if \"纳税人识别号\" in df.columns else \"\"\n\n        fname = f\"{safe_filename(district)}_\" \\\n                f\"{safe_filename(taxpayer_name)}_\" \\\n                f\"{safe_filename(taxpayer_id)}.xlsx\"\n        out_path = os.path.join(out_dir, fname)\n\n        # ---- 3.5 保存文件 ----\n        wb.save(out_path)\n        print(f\"生成：{out_path}\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    generate_forms()\n```\n\n---\n\n**你需要做的几件事：**\n\n1. **先把模板转成 xlsx**  \n   - 打开你发给我的 `欠税企业调查情况表3.17.xls`  \n   - 另存为：`欠税企业调查情况表模板.xlsx`  \n   - 放在和脚本同一目录下，或者改 `TEMPLATE_PATH` 为实际路径。\n\n2. **确认源数据列名**  \n   - 看一下你从 Impala 导出的表头（列名）。  \n   - 尽量让列名就叫：`纳税人识别号`、`纳税人名称`、`市（州）局`、`区县局` 等。  \n   - 如果名字不一样，就改脚本里 `FIELD_CELL_MAP` 左边的键，和 `DISTRICT_COLUMN` 的值。\n\n3. **确认区县局列的取值**  \n   - 源数据里区县局列（`DISTRICT_COLUMN`）的值最好就是：  \n     `自流井 / 贡井 / 大安 / 沿滩 / 荣县 / 富顺 / 高新`  \n   - 如果有其他写法（比如“自流井区税务局”），可以：\n     - 要么在 Impala SQL 里用 `case` 先归一化；\n     - 要么改 `DISTRICTS` 和 `DISTRICT_COLUMN` 的逻辑。\n\n4. **安装依赖并运行**（在你自己的环境里）  \n   - 安装：  \n     ```bash\n     pip install pandas openpyxl\n     ```  \n   - 运行脚本：  \n     ```bash\n     python 生成欠税企业调查表.py\n     ```  \n   - 跑完后，`OUTPUT_ROOT` 目录下会是这样的结构：  \n     - `输出_欠税企业调查情况表/自流井/*.xlsx`  \n     - `输出_欠税企业调查情况表/贡井/*.xlsx`  \n     - …  \n     - `输出_欠税企业调查情况表/高新/*.xlsx`  \n     - `输出_欠税企业调查情况表/其他/*.xlsx`（万一有意外区县）\n\n---\n\n如果你愿意，把你 Impala 导出的那张汇总表的**表头行**贴给我（或说明每一列代表什么），我可以帮你把 `FIELD_CELL_MAP` 精确对上每一列和模板中的位置，包括“税款追征入库合计”“清欠计划金额”等更细字段。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773997875506}}
